      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What is a Google Business Profile and why does it matter?</summary>
        <p>Your Google Business Profile (formerly Google My Business) is the listing that appears when someone searches your business name or searches for services you offer on Google Maps and in the local 3-pack. It shows your hours, reviews, photos, and contact info. If it is not optimized, you are invisible to local searchers — and your competitors are getting those calls instead.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How long does it take to see results?</summary>
        <p>Most businesses see measurable improvements in local search visibility within 30-60 days. The speed depends on your current profile state, competition level, and review volume. Businesses with strong review counts tend to see faster results.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do I need a physical storefront?</summary>
        <p>No. Service-area businesses — contractors, cleaners, mobile services, consultants — can set up a Google Business Profile without showing a physical address. We configure your service area correctly so you show up when nearby customers search.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What if I already have a profile but it is not ranking?</summary>
        <p>That is exactly who we work with most. We audit what you have, fix what is wrong, fill in what is missing, and build an ongoing strategy to keep you ranking — not just a one-time cleanup.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How is this different from SEO?</summary>
        <p>GBP optimization focuses specifically on your Google Maps and local search presence. <a href="/services/seo/">SEO</a> covers your website's organic rankings across all of Google. They work together — a strong GBP combined with good website SEO gives you both local and organic visibility. We offer both.</p>
      </details>

